<topic id="53a2b7c6-a269-4916-9313-bdc301ee9398" revisionNumber="1">
  <developerConceptualDocument xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
    <introduction address="intro">
      <para>This is used to insert a link to another conceptual topic using its
ID value.  It can also be used to create links to elements within the same
page that have an <codeInline>address</codeInline> attribute such as the
<codeInline>introduction</codeInline> and <codeInline>section</codeInline>
elements.</para>
    </introduction>

    <section>
      <title>Usage</title>
      <content>
        <para>For topic links, a link consists of a required
<codeInline>xlink:href</codeInline> attribute that contains the GUID of the
topic to which the link will go and optional inner text.  If no inner text is
specified, the text will be retrieved from the referenced topic's
<link xlink:href="cfd9dabf-22f3-4742-8b54-d84404610db1">companion file</link>.
If the companion file contains a <codeInline>linkText</codeInline> element, its
value will be used.  If not, the value of the <codeInline>title</codeInline>
element will be used.</para>
        <para>For in-page links, simply specify a hash character (#) followed by
the name of the anchor from an element's <codeInline>address</codeInline>
attribute.  Inner text is also required.</para>
        <alert class="note">
          <para>In order for the inner text to appear on topic links, you currently
need to use a custom version of the
<legacyBold>ResolveConceptualLinksComponent</legacyBold>.  The component is
integrated with <token>SHFB</token> and is also available in a standalone build
component download at the same site for use in third-party tools or your own
build scripts.</para>
        </alert>
        <alert class="note">
          <para>The custom build component also adds the ability to link to anchors
within a topic by adding a hash character (#) followed by the anchor name after
the GUID.</para>
        </alert>
        
        <alert class="tip">
        	<para>When used in a <codeInline>relatedTopics</codeInline>
element, an optional <codeInline>topicType_id</codeInline> attribute can be
added that specifies a GUID value used to classify the link type so that it is
grouped with other similar links.  See the
<link xlink:href="bfdd5115-f594-480d-9e79-af906e599337" /> topic for more
information.</para>
        </alert>
        
      </content>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Example</title>
      <content>
        <code language="xml" title=" ">
Self-closing: &lt;link xlink:href="cfd9dabf-22f3-4742-8b54-d84404610db1" /&gt;
With inner text: &lt;link xlink:href="cfd9dabf-22f3-4742-8b54-d84404610db1"&gt;
companion file&lt;/link&gt;
In-page link to introduction: &lt;link xlink:href="#intro"&gt;Back to Intro&lt;/link&gt;
Link to other topic anchor:
&lt;link xlink:href="dc4fcc96-283e-4202-9ecc-08a65e0c9313#BuildTools" /&gt;
</code>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Example Output</title>
      <content>
        <para>Self-closing: <link xlink:href="cfd9dabf-22f3-4742-8b54-d84404610db1" /></para>
        <para>With inner text: <link xlink:href="cfd9dabf-22f3-4742-8b54-d84404610db1">
companion file</link></para>
        <para>In-page link to introduction: <link xlink:href="#intro">Back to Intro</link></para>
        <para>Link to other topic anchor: <link xlink:href="dc4fcc96-283e-4202-9ecc-08a65e0c9313#BuildTools" /></para>
      </content>
    </section>

